The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, April 03, 2005 

 Chamling plea to Patil

 Gangtok, April 2: Chief minister Pawan Chamling today gave a memorandum to Union home minister Shivraj Patil reiterating the demand for reservation of seats for Limbus and Tamangs in the Assembly and raising the number of Assembly seats from 32 to 60, reports our correspondent.

 The memorandum to Patil, who is on a three-day visit to the state, also demanded that the number of Lok Sabha and Rajya Sabha seats be increased from the one each to two each. The demands also included a bonus of Rs 1,000 crore for the state for being ?the most peaceful? in the country.

 Chamling, who met Patil at Raj Bhavan this evening, also demanded the reopening of the trade route through the border post of Nathula. 




